intro: Tinnea gracilipedicellata, commonly known as the slender-footed tinnea, is a species of flowering plant in the family Myrtaceae. It is native to Australia and is characterized by its small, narrow leaves and clusters of white or pale pink flowers. The plant typically grows in sandy or rocky soils and is often found in coastal or inland regions. It produces small, woody fruits that contain several seeds, which are dispersed by wind. Due to its limited distribution and specific habitat requirements, it is considered a rare and ecologically significant species.
